fix(sdk,browser,recon,pentest,logcat): zip-slip guard, real header capture, header-delivered CSP

sdk.py (CRITICAL — zip-slip / tar-slip, CVE-2007-4559 class):
  * bootstrap_jdk and bootstrap_sdk called tarfile/zipfile extractall()
    with zero member validation; a malicious JDK or cmdline-tools mirror
    could write arbitrary files anywhere on the host.
  * Add _safe_extract_zip() and _safe_extract_tar() helpers. Every member
    is resolved against dest.resolve() and must relative_to() it; absolute
    paths and backslash traversal are rejected. Tar path prefers Python
    3.12+ extractall(filter="data") and falls back to per-member
    validation with symlink linkname checks.
  * Replace both extractall() calls and the hand-rolled loop in
    bootstrap_sdk (now _safe_extract_zip(..., strip_prefix="cmdline-tools/")).

browser.py + recon.py (HIGH — wrong headers + missed CSP):
  * analyze_security_headers / analyze_csp previously fetched headers via
    page-context JS (XHR/fetch), so every CORS-stripped response leaked
    into the report and header-delivered CSP was invisible (only meta was
    checked — missed 95% of real sites).
  * Browser now has main_frame_response_headers, populated during
    navigate() from buffered Network.responseReceived events for the
    first Document-typed response (Network.enable is now idempotent).
  * _capture_main_frame_headers reads that cache — no second fetch,
    no reload, no CORS filtering.
  * analyze_csp now consults Content-Security-Policy AND
    Content-Security-Policy-Report-Only from the real headers, falls back
    to meta, and surfaces warnings for meta-only and report-only CSP.
  * full_recon() now writes UTF-8.

pentest.py (MEDIUM):
  * PentestContext.report() now writes UTF-8 to avoid mojibake on
    non-ASCII payloads / titles.

logcat.py (MEDIUM):
  * find_crashes dedup was keyed on (event_type, message[:80]), which
    collapsed every ANR in the same app, every ASan SEGV on a different
    address, and every Java OOM into a single event. Key now includes
    pid and timestamp so distinct crashes are preserved.

Tests:
  * tests/test_sdk_extract.py — 9 cases: reject parent-dir traversal,
    absolute paths, backslash traversal; accept normal entries with and
    without strip_prefix; tar symlink and traversal rejection.
  * tests/test_recon.py — 6 cases: header cache drives
    analyze_security_headers; empty cache reports honestly; CSP from
    response header; report-only and meta-only surface warnings.
  * tests/test_logcat_dedup.py — 2 cases: distinct pids not collapsed;
    identical rows still deduped.

Suite: 134 passed, 1 skipped.
